Well I think the &quot;No&quot; hits a nerve on folks that have felt the pain. No SQL
hits a nerve with folks that have struggled around making relational dbs fit
for a set of scenarios. I does have an &quot;I&#39;m fed up&quot; notion to it though.

I don&#39;t think &quot;No REST&quot; would be appropriate here as it is not that folks
have tried REST in it&#39;s purity and struggled with it, they have with SOAP
though.

&quot;RESTful HTTP&quot; implies it is close to REST, on inspection though I don&#39;t
think it is. One is about exposing methods over the wire (RPC) and one
isn&#39;t.

My $.02
Glenn
